<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Edit:  Lol, just noticed I put this in the fashion thread.  Anyway, I have respect for people who wear goofy-looking outfits with good stats, because they're there to get the job done.  I also have respect for people who pay a lot of attention to fashion but also pay a lot of attention to their role in a group.  "I could play my character with no equipment on if I had to"<BR><BR>aaanyway...  on to my rant against the "200 WIS MINIMUM"<BR>/Edit<BR><BR>Extra wisdom and extra mana don't help you regain mana any quicker.  I tend towards AC in group situations based on the high taunt values of snares, debuffs and heals.  AC also helps when rooting mobs in close quarters.  Often, I believe it is the difference between needing a heal and being able to just regen back the hitpoints.  <BR><BR>Who goes FM to OOM on pulls?  "I wear wis gear because i'm constantly LOM" doesn't make sense to me.  Med up, quit casting group thorns or nukes, or tell the puller to slow his/her pulls down.  80M/175wis is a lot better than 40M/200wis.<BR><BR>In some cases, the life of the healer is more important than the life of a party member.  A party might be able to pull through if the puller dies, but the healer stays alive long enough to keep the tank and other crowd controllers alive.  Similarly, as evaccers, druids are responsible for keeping themselves alive so that they can whisk everyone to safety.  Neglecting AC/hp in favor of a deeper mana pool increases the risk of dying.  Adding AC/hp means you can cast the heal just a bit earlier because you'll survive that much longer before the situation is back under control.<BR><BR>/shrug - I agree with the high-end raid priorities though.<BR><BR>Yes, enlightened, mana-conserving druids can do wonders with 3000 mana / 740ac too, but they don't need to read my posts  <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR><BR>Most of the time, I go with:<BR>AC<BR>wis/hp/mana<BR>resists<BR>(on an item configurator, when 1 point of AC gets 8 points and 1 point of wis gets 10 points, the output seems about right to me)<BR><BR>The following AC buffs are stackable with the skin series:<BR>CLR: Shield of Words<BR>SHM: Shroud of Spirits<BR>ENC: Shadow, Augment<BR>RNG: Call of Earth<BR>PAL: Armor of Faith <BR>agi buffs also give slight AC bonuses.<BR><BR>-Quelm, 54 modestly equipped Wanderer (900+ / 175 in an average group)<BR>Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule<BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Quelm on 2001-08-02 18:37 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=184"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Quelm"></a>
