<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">*shrugs*  It's true, you need high AC gear if you haven't learned to control monster aggro in a grouping situation.<BR><BR>As for being LOM... well if I had the choice of preserving mana or casting a damage shield on a taunting warrior, I would go LOM.  Basically by the time you are LOM you should still have enough mana left to snare a monster or evac.  If your group is good, they can live through a fight with you medding (or casting only the bare essentials and medding).  Using mana to make the group more effective means just that... using mana  <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif">  Being LOM doesn't have to be the result of a single pull.  It just might be the result of a multiple of pulls.  I have yet to find an efficient puller who waits until everyone is FM before he pulls another. <BR><BR>Sure, you don't have to use mana and your group will probably do just fine, but if you don't use every trick you have to make yourself useful, it's possible you are just along for the ride.  Many 6 person groups could really do just fine with the right 4 or 5.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR> <BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Arienne on 2001-08-02 18:46 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=522"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Arienne"></a>
