<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Quelm->Arienne mana:regen:same<BR>more wis != more spells cast<BR><2 pages of quoted material with no interpretation to justify its placement><BR>j/k<BR><BR>Right, so, did you read the part about wisdom and mana not affecting the mana-regen rate?  One can cast the same spells with 175 wisdom as with 200.  +wis/+mana only give you a larger mana pool, NOT the ability to cast more spells over time.  (This is why people complain about the inequality between caster and melee gear.)  <BR><BR>Also, I've found that some of the tricks in the druid books require more AC than mana.  Rooting extras, taunting off an enchanter, taking a few hits to let pack regens work more effectively, and evaccing when *everyone* has a mob to play with are all dangerous activities.  I agree that one should try to do as much as possible to help out a party, but I don't think that a high mana / low ac setup has as many options as a more balanced suit.<BR><BR>-Quelm, 54 Wanderer<BR>Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=184"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Quelm"></a>
