<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Telelial Telemancer</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Newbie</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Aug 01, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 3</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-08-02 20:18&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">If you think that having a lower wis is going to make you just as usefull in a group as a person with a higher wis then I dunno how you survived for so long. At this point I have over a 200 wis and have had for a long time (also I have over 800ac unbuffed with no ac/mana gear on). If I were in a group where someone over pulled and the chanter is having a tough time mezzing adds and the cleric is having to heal both the chanter and the melee, I would be adding my heals and damage shields to the cleric to help out. In this sitution mana regen rate and any other Sh** isnt going to help you out, the bigger your mana pool is, the more heals you can get off, simple as that. <BR><BR>In a raid sitution the more mana you have the more effective you are (that combined with resists and ac). Say you are fighting a dragon/giant/other anon uber mob in a raid. You are designated with being the druid who is to debuff it. You cast ros on the mob, then cast Fixation and/or Breath of ro, do you think your gonna sit for a good while after that? No. You are going to have to stand, and while standing you regen less mana so screw mana regen rate. Your next job is to the help clerics heal the main tank/tanks so they dont crap out and the mob beats on you the very next round. Therefor, the more mana you have, the less you have to med to be more effective.<BR><BR>So by all means, go ahead and have a lower wis/whatever, and see how your tanks/group likes it when your the only one who can heal/snare/evac/DS/finishing nuke, when you dont have enough mana because you didnt wanna get hit a lil bit. Im sure your gonna be loved alot.<BR><BR>Btw, not a flame, just simple facts.</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=1359"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=