<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Quelm, <BR>It's true that the mana pool doesn't affect the mana regen rate, but if you are grouped with other casters you will have time to med to full or closer to it.  I would still rather start off with 3 or 4 bubbles of mana at 200+ wisdom than 180 wisdom.  It's rare that a group would concerned about the druid's mana level if there is a cleric around, but I would still rather have the opportunity to have the most mana possible when medded to full.<BR><BR>I don't believe I ever said that AC was not important.  Only that Wisdom was a preference.  But back to the question at hand... if the original poster has a chioce between appearances and wisdom, I would recommend wisdom since that is the choice that will make him most effective for his options.  <BR><BR>It's only my opinion... and yes, it's smarts that will really will make you the most effective, but smarts also means that a druid doesn't often get hit.  We have a lot of the same aggro management issues that most casters have.  Also, a lot of the getting hit part is dependent on the group smarts as well.  If a monster is rooted or mezzed and I snare and sunder or fixate it, I HOPE that the warrior will taunt a bit before breaking the root or mez.  If there is no warrior, I change my tactics.  <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=522"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Arienne"></a>
